\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11}{\ignorespaces Side-by-side Mollweide projections of Planck PR3 SMICA (left, smoothed to \(1^\circ \) FWHM) and a TFPT v4.12 random realisation (right, Mode A from \(C_\ell ^{\mathrm  {TFPT},v4.12}\), seed 0, \(N_{\mathrm  {side}}=1024\), smoothed to \(1^\circ \)). Colour scale \(\pm 300\,\mu \mathrm  {K}\). The two skies are statistically indistinguishable at the eyeball level --- exactly as expected, because the v4.12 \(C_\ell \) match Planck to within \(\Delta (-2\ln L)=+0.61\) and Mode A injects independent random phases.}}{31}{figure.caption.11}\protected@file@percent }
